## ⚠️ Items needing Chris call before this proposal merges into `roadmap.md`

The marketing agent flagged three items where it can't unilaterally decide:

1. **Is the 2026-06-08 Android / 2026-06-29 iOS launch date public-shareable?**
   Currently flagged in "Internal — never publish." If you want T-30 build-in-public posts, this needs to flip. Recommend: keep internal until ~T-14 then start public T-minus messaging.

2. **Junction "60 days" claim in the social-launch.md pinned-tweet drafts.**
   Soften to "coming" in any draft until Junction sandbox + B2B contract actually land. Don't commit to a 60-day window publicly without that backing.

3. **Chase + Stripe live activation timing.**
   Currently paused; affects "Stripe live billing" framing if anyone asks about web purchases at launch. Recommend: don't reference Stripe in launch copy at all; RevenueCat IAP is the path.

