## How to apply this proposal

If you accept all three flagged items as captured above (default: keep launch dates internal, soften Junction, don't reference Stripe):

```bash
mv ~/projects/biotica-web/docs/marketing/roadmap.md.proposed \
   ~/projects/biotica-web/docs/marketing/roadmap.md
git -C ~/projects/biotica-web add docs/marketing/roadmap.md
git -C ~/projects/biotica-web commit -m "docs(marketing): roadmap sync 2026-05-08 — WS3.1 + workout rehash + paywall + DUNS + email auth"
```

If you want to flip the launch-date item to public, edit the "Coming next" section's `[NEEDS CHRIS CALL]` flag before applying.

Re-upload to the Claude.ai marketing project (Knowledge → replace `roadmap.md`) once the file is committed — the agent flow doesn't replace the project's static knowledge until the 30-day sunset completes.
